        <div class="faq__answer" id="kitchen-sink-e5-tool-faq-a5" data-open="false">
          <p>Then the monthly fee isn&rsquo;t your first question. Catching up or cleaning up historical books is separate one-time work &mdash; cleanup runs $1,500&ndash;$15,000+ and catch-up $2,000&ndash;$20,000+, priced on how far behind you are and the severity of the issues. Once the books are current, the monthly fee this tool estimates takes over.</p>
